    <h3 class="comment__title"><a href="/comment/567033#comment-567033" class="permalink" rel="bookmark">vagal tone and heart rate variability</a></h3>
  
  <div class="submitted subtext">
    Submitted by Don G on November 8, 2013 - 12:45pm  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden">
        <div class="field__item"><p>Very interesting article. I've been looking into vagal tone and heart rate variability (the heart's speeding up and slowing down as you breathe) as it relates to anxiety and have found the EmWave2 by Heart Math to be really helpful in training variability and controlling stress responses. It basically gives you feedback on how your emotional state is affecting your autonomic nervous system.</p>
</div>
