        <div class="field__item"><p>Thanks for a very interesting article.</p>
<p>Will just mention that Tai Chi too is a good practice with regards to the healthy function of the Vagus Nerve.</p>
<p>I have also found that relaxing as much as possible (i.e. isolating the muscles that are actually needed) during aerobic exercise (biking, rowing, swimming etc) immediately lowers the heart rate - at the same time as the result (distance covered) is enhanced.</p>
<p>In my experience, this principle plays into all aspects of life. There is only one balance point at all times. </p>
<p>Thanks again!</p>
