    <h3 class="comment__title"><a href="/comment/689951#comment-689951" class="permalink" rel="bookmark">Dr. Stephen Porges - Polyvagal Theory</a></h3>
  
  <div class="submitted subtext">
    Submitted by Join the Resilience! on November 16, 2014 - 4:43pm  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden">
        <div class="field__item"><p>Great article! You and your readers might be interested in the Polyvagal Theory developed by Dr. Stephen Porges.</p>
<p>His evolutionary model of the ANS is hierarchical based on 2 branches of the vagus nerve, one reptilian/ancient, the other mammalian/new.</p>
<p>So.... the ANS model has 3 levels:</p>
<p>Parasympathetic - Social Engagement (Safety) - New Vagus</p>
<p>          Sympathetic - Arousal (possible danger)</p>
<p>Parasympathetic - Shutdown/Freeze (Life Threatening) - Old Vagus</p>
<p>Go crazy on Google and YouTube, you'll find a ton of info.</p>
<p>It all ties back to what you wrote about Christopher. Cool stuff!</p>
<p>Join the Resilience!</p>
</div>
  </div>
      </div>

