    <h3 class="comment__title"><a href="/comment/689968#comment-689968" class="permalink" rel="bookmark">Vasovagal Syncope</a></h3>
  
  <div class="submitted subtext">
    Submitted by AnonymousIdiot on November 16, 2014 - 6:27pm  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden">
        <div class="field__item"><p>I think that it is good practice to warn people about the possibility of fainting when utilising deep breaths. If you take a deep breath and push down toward your stomach you can get light headed because your heart has slowed down so much that it momentarily limits the blood to the brain. This can lead to fainting. It's not dangerous but it's good to expect it so you don't bump your head.</p>
</div>
  </div>
      </div>

