    <h3 class="comment__title"><a href="/comment/827989#comment-827989" class="permalink" rel="bookmark">Vagus nerve Stimulator </a></h3>
  
  <div class="submitted subtext">
    Submitted by Kara Moore on March 21, 2016 - 7:40pm  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden">
        <div class="field__item"><p>Since my post almost 3 years ago I am still accumulating sobriety time. I continue to do investigation on the vagus nerve just because I know what VNS has done for me. How it took me from chronic alcoholism to a life beyond my wildest dreams. Since VNS I started craving physical fitness challenges. I started running. I just ran a marathon on the 14th of Feb. Most importantly VNS has controlled my seizures. I can stop a seizure mid stream with one swipe of my magnetic bracelet I wear at all time. I also started meditation in the fall of last year. Meditation is helping with any anger issues that arrive from time to time. Your vagus nerve can also get you worked up in frustration when things do not go your way. I can calm myself down shortly thereafter too. My vagus nerve is also getting battery powered electricity sent to it every 3 mins. to help prevent seizures and the auras that go along with it. So aerobic exercise and meditation help calm you down and give you an overall sense of comfort, ease, and well-being. Before VNS I never had an athletic bone in my body.  Today I am running marathons.</p>
