<div class="comment comment-by-anonymous clearfix">
  
    <h3 class="comment__title"><a href="/comment/849297#comment-849297" class="permalink" rel="bookmark">Vagus nerve</a></h3>
  
  <div class="submitted subtext">
    Submitted by Steve on June 7, 2016 - 3:20pm  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden">
        <div class="field__item"><p>I have practised yoga, tai chi and aikido for over 40 years now and, as you can imagine, have heard quite a few pre-scientific, unsubstantiated claims made about their health benefits. Recently though I developed a highly debilitating autoimmune condition. Cortico steroids got me moving again but tai chi and chi kung reenergise and give relief from muscle stiffness and pain for 2 hours or more daily. Perhaps they have helped me to reduce the required dose and mitigated against some of the side effects of the steroids as well.  What I have read about the vagus nerve could give me a way of thinking about the link in a modern and considered way. For what it's worth, I suspect that tai chi / chi kung stimulate the vagus nerve which then ameliorates the symptoms of my condition rather than cures the underlying problem. However, it's all good and I look forward to seeing some research on the subject.</p>
</div>
  </div>
      </div>

